modules.description: Provides functions for reading from and writing to file descriptors using bigstring data structures. Operates on byte sequences with efficient memory handling for large data transfers. Enables low-level I/O operations in network and file processing tasks.

Provides functions to read from and write to file descriptors using bigstrings, which are efficient byte arrays. It supports memory-mapping files for direct access and manipulation, with options for shared memory and custom offsets. Used for high-performance I/O operations, such as processing large binary files or inter-process communication.
